text.tspan: Change in prevalence of alcohol use disorders by age, World, 1990 to 2017
Share of the population within particular age categories suffering from alcohol use disorders. Alcohol dependence
is defined by the International Classification of Diseases as the presence of three or more indicators of dependence
for at least a month within the previous year.
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease
